"{\"uid\": \"independent.ie-irish-news-team-ireland-wins-bronze-in-international-culinary-olympics-competition-a530098896.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Junior Team Ireland with their bronze medals including Dubliner Chris Leech (fifth from left)  Team Ireland took home a bronze medal at the Culinary Olympics in Germany after battling it out against 66 other nations.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988090167, \"rank\": 1.1903350709921676e-09, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.995995583111265, \"rank\": 0.002672570634556539, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 1,800 chefs took part in the international showcase event in Stuttgart this month, cooking a full three-course meal for 75 people in the junior category and 110 in the senior category.\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 284, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuttgart\", \"score\": 0.9999702936990157, \"rank\": 2.5969686865179966e-05, \"text\": \"Stuttgart\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuttgart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuttgart\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Ireland junior captain Chris Leech (24), who is from the village of Naul in north County Dublin described the win as a \\\"phenomenal achievement for a small nation\\\".\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988090167, \"rank\": 1.1903350709921676e-09, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naul,_Dublin\", \"score\": 0.8259079200079165, \"rank\": 0.17582417582416687, \"text\": \"Naul\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naul,_Dublin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naul,_Dublin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are over the moon.\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It really shows that hard work pays off.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We only signed up eight months ago and had a small budget unlike many of the bigger nations,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Leech is a sous chef for catering company Sodexo.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 792, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following in his father's career path, Mr Leech started off with a catering company while in transition year, and worked his way up through culinary school and worked under world renowned chef Raymond Blanc in the UK.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 1018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 1007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Blanc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Raymond Blanc\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Blanc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Blanc\"}, {\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999982354399543, \"rank\": 1.7599004821289048e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was thrown into the deep end from the start.\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was really green while working for him and just soaked up everything like a sponge, writing everything down,\\\" he told theIrish Independent.\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1197, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999972319529, \"rank\": 2.6867407416543217e-09, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After getting the call from the panel of chefs of Ireland, who chose the team through a combination of assessments, Mr Leech travelled to Limerick each week where the team trained for the Culinary Olympics.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9997009979749097, \"rank\": 0.0002990630245144608, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limerick\", \"score\": 0.9955295236473435, \"rank\": 0.003974504375149897, \"text\": \"Limerick\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limerick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limerick\"}, {\"begin\": 1399, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Exhibition_of_Culinary_Art\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Culinary Olympics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Exhibition_of_Culinary_Art\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Exhibition_of_Culinary_Art\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They worked on different recipes and dish development for seven or eight hours each session, refining their work over an eight month period, compared to other nations who prepared over the last four years.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition, which took place between February 3-7, required teams to cook a full-three course from the 'Restaurant of Nations' menu with 70 plates going out, four of these being to unknown judges.\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams were graded based on their service, plates and overall taste, with the main grading going towards consistency.\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Leech said this year judges threw a \\\"curveball\\\" calling for a vegan starter for the very first time.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The junior team delivered a confit butternut squash fondant with an avocado chilli mousse, a special cracker and pickles on top.\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the main course, they delivered pork fillets wrapped in a burnt leek powder, carrot pur\\u00e9e, roast carrots, a potato terrine, raised pork belly croquette, and a cabbage ball with streaky bacon and \\\"loads of butter\\\".\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams cooked in specially-fitted glass-walled kitchens with visitors scrutinising their every move.\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Generally I do not work well in big groups.\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a little daunting when you would be focused and working away and all of a sudden you look up and 400 or 500 people are just staring at you,\\\" Mr Leech said.\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Ireland was made up of a senior panel and junior panel as well as two helpers, amounting to 24 people in total, with little to no fans present.\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999988090167, \"rank\": 1.1903350709921676e-09, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They faced giants such as Sweden, South Korea and Canada who each brought four teams and close to 500 spectators.\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2887, \"end\": 2893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.998559181452452, \"rank\": 0.0009506905570103032, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}, {\"begin\": 2895, \"end\": 2906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999984565363863, \"rank\": 7.359663429111791e-07, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2911, \"end\": 2917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999075853083607, \"rank\": 8.761150742653654e-05, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We had zero coverage,\\\" Mr Leech said.\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the next IKA Culinary Olympics is not for another four years' time, the Dublin native hopes that Ireland, who begin training for it from next week, can get more people, bigger names as well as sponsors and achieve even more in terms of medals.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3118, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9997009979749097, \"rank\": 0.0002990630245144608, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ireland's restaurant and food quality is on the rise.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9997009979749097, \"rank\": 0.0002990630245144608, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have gained 15 or 16 Michelin stars in the last five years, which is phenomenal for such a small country.\", \"from\": 3321, \"to\": 3429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3345, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.970718900896005e-17, \"text\": \"Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With the right resources we can do a hell of a lot better next time around,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 3431, \"to\": 3518, \"entities\": []}]}"